<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/565005071/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Progressive Evaluation:
The students must attend the laboratory practices (minimum 80% attendance).); deliver individually the results of the practical work in the format and deadline indicated by the professor. The partial weights of each of the individual work are distributed as follows:
Computer aided Design (CAD) (W1). Weight 15% of final mark of the laboratory practices.
Part material selection (PART) (W2). Weight 15% of final mark of the laboratory practices.
Tools material selection (TOOL) (W3). Weight 15% of final mark of the laboratory practices.
Computer aided Machining (CAM) (W4). Weight: 55% of the final mark of the laboratory practices.
To pass the course the following conditions must be necessary:
Perform all of laboratory practices throughout the semester.
Obtain a minimum mark of 4 points out of 10 in the individual works.
Obtain a final mark at least 5 points out of 10. This final mark must be equal to the weighted sum of the marks obtained in the individual works.
Extraordinary Call
For the extraordinary call, students will take an exam, that will contain short questions, demonstrations, practical cases and/or numerical exercises. There will also be an individual test that will be done by computer consisting of practical cases similar to those made in the laboratory. The final mark will be the one obtained in this exam and will have a 100% weight on the final marke. To pass the subject it will be necessary to have attended at least 80% of the practical classes and a mark equal to or greater than 5 points out of 10 in the written exam."""@es ;
